40|$|Activities of Companies in Japan are {{affected}} by many laws. The Constitution of Japan emphasizes the respect of fundamental human rights does control some rights and obligations of the companies. However, the <b>Companies</b> <b>Law</b> is the main law for them. It is the <b>law</b> for <b>companies,</b> stockholders and creditors and explains {{the relationship between the}} three parties. In particular, it regards stability of the trading as important. The <b>Companies</b> <b>Law</b> is a special law of the Civil Code. Therefore the <b>Companies</b> <b>law</b> overrides the Civil Code. But it lacks some important statutes, for instance, the good faith principle and the abuse of rights doctrine. In this situation, the Civil Code applies to the companies as the general law of private laws...|$|R
